Introduction

cosmosy is a four-member global girl group under NTT Docomo Studio & Live and Sony Music Entertainment Korea. They first debuted in Japan on December 31, 2024 and globally on February 7, 2025 with the digital single "zigy=zingy"', and later officially on April 11, 2025 with the digital single "Lucky=One".

Their group name, "cosmosy" symbolizes the "infinity of cosmos" and the "possibilities of youth". The group also sing in three languages: Japanese, English, and Korean.

Prior to their debut with the group, De_Hana and Kamión were both known for being contestants on Produce 101 Japan The Girls, where they got eliminated in episode 10 after ranking 30th and 24th place respectively. On the contrary, Himesha and A’mei weren't known before their debut in cosmosy.
